TITLE: US Army falls 25% short of recruiting goal
SUMMARY: The U.S. Army fell short of its recruitment goal by 25% this year, as Air Force, Marine Corps and Navy dipped into pools of delayed entry applicants to meet goals.

TITLE: Hurricane Ian response: I-75 in Florida closes, cutting off key supply route
SUMMARY: A portion of I-75, a critical Florida thoroughfare, was closed due to flooding from the Myakka River. The closure cut off a key supply route after Hurricane Ian.

TITLE: Hurricane Ian: Florida personnel go door to door warning of possible levee break in Sarasota County
SUMMARY: Florida authorities are warning residents of a possible levee break in Sarasota County. A notification alerted that there was a potential of 15 feet of flood water.

TITLE: Lifetime's Gabby Petito movie fills gaps with dramatizations but hits these authentic notes
SUMMARY: Lifetime's "The Gabby Petito Story" is a true-crime drama â€“ with fictional moments bridging the gaps in the real tragedy with ex-fiance Brian Laundrie.

TITLE: London coroner rules 14-year-old girl's death suicide resulting from social media: 'The Wild West era is over'
SUMMARY: A London coroner on Friday ruled 14-year-old Molly Russell's 2017 death "an act of self harm while suffering from depression and the negative effects of online content."

TITLE: Las Vegas shooting: Former officer reflects on 5 years since 58 people shot dead at country festival
SUMMARY: A retired Las Vegas police officer reflects on the heroism displayed during the Oct. 1, 2017, shooting into the Route 91 Harvest Festival that left a total of 60 people dead.

TITLE: Georgia's Debbie Collier case: Timeline of events in burned office manager's slaying
SUMMARY: Debbie Collier, a Georgia real estate office manager, went missing on Sept. 10 and was discovered dead under suspicious circumstances the following day.

TITLE: Bodycam footage shows New York State Police rescue teen from burning car: 'Prevented a tragedy'
SUMMARY: New York State Police released footage of the moment two troopers rescued an unresponsive 17-year-old driver from a vehicle engulfed in flames in the town of Wappinger.

TITLE: Washington, DC police officers under investigation after confiscating guns without making arrests
SUMMARY: Seven D.C. police officers and supervisors are being probed after allegedly confiscating firearms without making arrests. They have been placed on non-contact status.

TITLE: Michigan man charged in connection to shooting of elderly pro-life volunteer
SUMMARY: A Michigan homeowner was charged Friday after shooting and injuring an 84-year-old pro-life woman who was canvassing door-to-door against a ballot measure.
